  "original_title": "12 \u0baf\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vimal's letter to President Ranil presenting 12 ideas",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "National Freedom Front leader and Colombo District Member of Parliament Vimal Weerawansa has sent a letter to President Ranil Wickremesinghe presenting 12 ideas.",
        "He has mentioned in the letter that he is confident that the country will travel on the right path if the ideas are implemented and his party is ready to provide cooperation if the ideas are carried forward.",
        "\uf0b7 Establishment of Parliamentary Select Committee to look into people's struggle and people's security along with establishing the rule of law in the country",
        "\uf0b7 Conducting All-Party Leaders' Conference to resolve current issues and formulate long-term policy plan.",
        "\uf0b7 Formulate a special program to implement the ideas of the advocates and technical experts in the struggle of the All Party Conference.",
        "\uf0b7 Resolving the political and economic crisis and ensuring a secure environment for free and fair elections.",
        "\uf0b7 Formation of a government acceptable to all parties following the All Party Conference.",
        "\uf0b7 Publicizing the truth among the people about the economic condition of the country.",
        "\uf0b7 Acting on public policy. With the size of the cabinet fixed at 30 to control government expenditure, the cabinet is required to meet twice a week.",
        "\uf0b7 Establishment of Parliamentary Select Committee to seek input of Members of Parliament on Cabinet issues and resolutions",
        "Meanwhile, President Ranil Wickresinghe had a separate phone conversation with National Freedom Front leader Vimal Weerawansa, Lanka Sama Samayak Party leader Prof. Thissa Vidarana, Comnews Party deputy leader Weerasumana Weerasinghe.",
        "During this, issues including all-party government were discussed. However, the leaders of the said parties said that confirmation regarding the implementation of the ideas mentioned in the letter sent by Vimal Weerawansavin is necessary and an official call should be made regarding the all-party government."
      ],
